Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.18,0:00:03.85,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Alice is missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.06,0:00:09.32,Default,Rinko,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes. I've been worried\Nthat she may be doing too much.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.78,0:00:13.82,Default,Rinko,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}But every time I ask,\N"Are you tired? Do you need to rest?"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.82,0:00:16.53,Default,Rinko,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}she just smiles and shakes her head.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.12,0:00:20.41,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'll head over there for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.75,0:00:26.00,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Then we'll be better able to take action\Nas soon as we hear from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.80,0:00:35.80,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.43,0:00:42.39,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Alice!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.98,0:00:48.81,Default,Deliveryman,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Large package for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.94,0:00:54.53,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,From Rath?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.99,0:00:56.66,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.89,0:01:21.76,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Would you kindly stop making a such a scene\Nand pull me out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.18,0:01:23.27,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Kirito?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.97,0:01:27.98,Default,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,New World
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.40,0:01:37.11,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Alice, why would you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.03,0:01:42.37,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I am sorry for escaping like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.24,0:01:48.75,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,But I was desperate to speak with you alone,\Nface-to-face,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.75,0:01:52.21,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,not in your virtual form,\Nbut as someone with a real body.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.80,0:01:53.75,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Kirito...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.59,0:01:56.42,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I am angry with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.84,0:01:59.30,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Why didn't you tell me that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.76,0:02:02.43,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That it might be our final farewell?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.85,0:02:06.60,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If only you'd told me that\Nat the World's End Altar, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.06,0:02:08.14,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.85,0:02:11.31,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I would not have fled on my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.52,0:02:15.07,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I am a knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.28,0:02:18.15,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Someone whose destiny is to fight! So...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:23.03,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,why did you choose to face\Nsuch a dreadful foe all alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:26.95,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,and why didn't you want me by your side?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.29,0:02:35.50,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Who am I, Alice Synthesis Thirty, in your eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.09,0:02:37.76,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,What am I to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.05,0:02:44.89,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.56,0:02:47.06,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,my hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.68,0:02:50.44,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,And not just my hope, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.44,0:02:54.32,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,For all those scores of people who lived\Nand died in that world, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.32,0:02:56.19,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,you're our irreplaceable hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.19,0:02:59.78,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I couldn't bear to lose you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:01.03,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,That hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.49,0:03:03.24,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to link it to the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.95,0:03:07.95,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,The future...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.58,0:03:12.00,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly will the future look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.58,0:03:17.42,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,After I've endured the endless loneliness\Nof living in the chaos of the real world,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.42,0:03:21.68,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,inside this unwieldy steel-element body,\Nwhat could possibly be awaiting me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.05,0:03:27.64,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Sorry. Even I don't know that yet, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.56,0:03:35.94,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}you being here will change the world.\NYou're the one who will change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.52,0:03:44.16,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}And when all is said and done,\NCardinal's, Administrator's, Bercouli's, Eldrie's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.87,0:03:50.12,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}and Eugeo's hopes will finally be rewarded.\NI have no doubt of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.42,0:03:58.46,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,We must let Dr. Rinko know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.26,0:04:02.42,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't do to make her worry so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.72,0:04:05.76,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.14,0:04:10.02,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:12.56,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,She's much calmer now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:15.35,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.69,0:04:16.77,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.61,0:04:22.65,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, she wasn't mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.65,0:04:25.74,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, she said she felt bad for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.95,0:04:30.24,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,And she said that you can spend the night here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.45,0:04:33.33,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.54,0:04:34.50,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.50,0:04:38.21,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'd like you\Nto show me around this house first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.09,0:04:45.05,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen any traditional buildings\Nin the real world before!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.05,0:04:47.14,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Sure... no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.47,0:04:53.02,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,But... it's just a family home,\Nso it's not like there's a lot to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.19,0:04:55.27,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.85,0:04:57.52,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,I know where to take you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.99,0:05:09.28,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.58,0:05:12.37,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,a training hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.37,0:05:15.92,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Over here, we call it a dojo, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.50,0:05:17.79,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Dojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.72,0:05:29.39,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,This is a wooden training sword, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.85,0:05:32.56,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,It's so different\Nfrom the ones in the Underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.98,0:05:40.06,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.36,0:05:41.57,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.15,0:05:45.53,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,What else would one do in a training hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.70,0:05:49.95,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,But Alice...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.62,0:05:52.49,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,in that body, you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.79,0:05:55.00,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,No need to hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.13,0:06:05.76,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.76,0:06:10.59,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Of that day when I first crossed swords with you\Nin the garden on the cathedral's eightieth floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.97,0:06:13.56,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,You really clobbered me that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.81,0:06:15.85,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,It won't happen again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.89,0:06:54.22,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,I win, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.68,0:06:57.89,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,And the winning move was the secret skill,\NSteel Headbutt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.31,0:07:01.23,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of that move.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.23,0:07:02.73,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,I just created it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.07,0:07:10.28,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Kirito. I'll be fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.91,0:07:12.91,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I know I can live in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.45,0:07:17.58,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}As long as I can wield a sword,\Nwherever I may be, I will be myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:19.71,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I've just realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.87,0:07:23.17,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,that my battle isn't over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.75,0:07:25.42,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,And neither is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.59,0:07:31.88,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}So I will look forward, and only forward,\Nand keep moving ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.47,0:07:35.68,Default,Suguha,0000,0000,0000,,So then, Big Brother fell, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:38.85,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Really? So even Kirito was once like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.85,0:07:41.56,Default,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, Kazuto could be\Nsuch a handful back then!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.77,0:07:46.27,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuto, we have a lot to talk about,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.57,0:07:50.99,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,but first I want to hear you say\Nwhat needs to be said.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.87,0:08:05.50,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, Mom. I'm really sorry\Nthat I made you worry yet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:07.96,Default,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,We're used to it by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.46,0:08:12.97,Default,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,And didn't you accomplish\Nsomething really important this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.13,0:08:18.97,Default,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,When a person agrees to take on an article— a job,\Nthey have to see it through to the end, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.35,0:08:21.31,Default,Suguha,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, you're making it personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.31,0:08:24.27,Default,Minetake,0000,0000,0000,,That might be your mother's take on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.69,0:08:29.23,Default,Minetake,0000,0000,0000,,but you have no idea how much stress\Nshe was under while you were missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.61,0:08:32.82,Default,Minetake,0000,0000,0000,,I get that it was a crucial mission,\Nand you got it done,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.82,0:08:34.70,Default,Minetake,0000,0000,0000,,but that doesn't mean you can just forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.03,0:08:38.41,Default,Minetake,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuto, what is your duty?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.41,0:08:40.29,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Being a high school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.54,0:08:41.95,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.95,0:08:46.75,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,And so it should be clear where you should\Nbe putting all of your effort right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.38,0:08:50.21,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,To study, and to get into college.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.21,0:08:52.84,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,It's already the summer of your junior year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.84,0:08:56.51,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother mentioned that\Nyou were looking to study abroad in America.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.51,0:08:58.01,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,Have you made any progress?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.05,0:09:01.02,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Well, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.31,0:09:06.23,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I want to change my focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:08.44,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,Please explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.86,0:09:12.11,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,I want to enter the electrical engineering department\Nat a Japanese university,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.11,0:09:14.24,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,preferably the Toto Institute of Technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.74,0:09:17.11,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I'd like to work at Rath—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.11,0:09:22.08,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,no, I mean the Oceanic Resource Exploration\N& Research Institution.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.46,0:09:32.46,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.67,0:09:34.13,Default,Suguha,0000,0000,0000,,"Father"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.13,0:09:40.10,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,My own father never forgave me\Nfor choosing to become a knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.26,0:09:44.06,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,But by making my own beliefs clear\Nthrough my actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.06,0:09:48.06,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,I am convinced that in the end,\Nhe came to understand that choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.35,0:09:49.23,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Kirito...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.73,0:09:53.94,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,I mean Kazuto, is someone\Nwho can follow the path he believes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.24,0:09:57.36,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,And that's because, despite being\Nan ordinary student in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.78,0:10:01.74,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,in that other world he was, without question,\Nthe most powerful swordsman of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.41,0:10:06.91,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's a hero who fought gallantly\Nto protect an untold number of residents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.16,0:10:08.29,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Alice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.33,0:10:10.42,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Alice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.34,0:10:14.55,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,His mother and I already know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.92,0:10:18.34,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuto's already a hero in this world, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:20.30,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Black Swordsman?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.85,0:10:22.97,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuto.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.43,0:10:28.52,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,To choose your path, study, take exams,\Nadvance to college, and then get a job,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.52,0:10:30.98,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,all of those things are just part of a process.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.98,0:10:34.11,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,But at the same time,\Nthey're also the fruits of your labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.44,0:10:38.74,Default,Minetaka,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you feel lost or uncertain at times,\Ntry to live with no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.66,0:10:46.04,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,I promise to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.45,0:10:49.71,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Dad, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.26,0:11:04.26,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Kirito.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.97,0:11:07.47,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Please wake up, Kirito.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.69,0:11:19.45,Default,Kirito,0000,0000,0000,,A-Alice—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.86,0:11:21.32,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Please lower your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.70,0:11:28.29,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, it's just that,\Nthis is kind of inappropriate, or should I say—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.25,0:11:32.50,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please don't look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.55,0:11:39.38,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,So, what happened this late?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.76,0:11:41.26,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,About five minutes ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.26,0:11:45.64,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,I received an alarming communication\Nthrough the remote messaging art...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.64,0:11:49.52,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,or rather, it came to me over the "network."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:51.39,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,An email? From whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.81,0:11:54.06,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,There was no name in the sender line.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.19,0:11:55.40,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,As for the content...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.94,0:11:58.78,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,rather than hear me read it,\Nit'd be better for you to see for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:08.99,Default,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an1}[Climb the white tower, and ye shall reach unto yon world.\NTraining Hall #2.Media Storage.Senate.Geographical Records Room]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:10.66,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.76,0:12:21.76,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Yui, are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.01,0:12:25.22,Default,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Daddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.72,0:12:28.01,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to wake you up, Yui.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.85,0:12:30.10,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Can you take a look at this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.77,0:12:37.36,Default,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,These are the names of the floors\Nin the Central Cathedral, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.36,0:12:38.19,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.52,0:12:43.07,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Training Hall #2 is on the fifty-second floor,\NMedia Storage is on the sixty-eighth floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.07,0:12:45.24,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,the senate is on the ninety-sixth floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.24,0:12:47.66,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,and the Geographical Records Room\Nis on the fifty-eighth floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.04,0:12:52.79,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.37,0:12:55.00,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,...an IP address?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.29,0:12:56.21,Default,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.00,0:13:02.21,Default,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,I think that the white tower to be climbed\Nrefers to the address in the second line.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.38,0:13:05.80,Default,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,And when you've climbed to the top,\Nyou reach "yon world."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.80,0:13:10.31,Default,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the server\Nthis address is pointing to is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.68,0:13:13.39,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:17.15,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Alice, this connects to that world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.11,0:13:20.61,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,It's the path to the Underworld!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.82,0:13:23.94,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Connects... path.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.11,0:13:30.08,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean that I can go—\NI mean, return home? To that world...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.74,0:13:32.79,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,To my world?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.00,0:13:35.00,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.88,0:13:47.09,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}By the way, Alice,\Nwhen we do go back to the Underworld,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.26,0:13:51.51,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}um, is it okay if we bring Asuna along, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.64,0:13:56.19,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I suppose not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.39,0:14:01.44,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}If there's an unexpected emergency,\Nwe'll need as many fighters as we can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:06.36,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:14.33,Default,Rinko,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Most likely, he's involved in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.70,0:14:17.04,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.34,0:14:25.51,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Yui. Did you find out anything about that address?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.76,0:14:29.05,Default,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I got as far as the server's relay point,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.05,0:14:32.72,Default,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but it has such a robust firewall\Nthat I can't dig any deeper.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.97,0:14:35.27,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.27,0:14:37.39,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we're heading out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.60,0:14:39.31,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,We won't be in any danger this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.81,0:14:40.86,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.86,0:14:43.77,Default,Yui,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If something happens,\NI'll come to save you right away!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:47.32,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you. All right, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.53,0:14:52.28,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Remember, it's been 200 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.58,0:14:56.20,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,There's no telling what's become\Nof the Human Empire and the land of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.54,0:14:58.25,Default,Kazuto,0000,0000,0000,,Be on your guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.46,0:15:02.92,Default,Asuna,0000,0000,0000,,Administrator ruled over the Human Empire\Nfor three hundred years, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.92,0:15:05.13,Default,Asuna,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't been as long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.42,0:15:07.38,Default,Asuna,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it hasn't changed that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.09,0:15:12.76,Default,Asuna,0000,0000,0000,,Once we're back,\Nlet's go wake up Selka first, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.60,0:15:18.52,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Kirito, Asuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.69,0:15:21.85,Default,Rinko,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.15,0:15:23.81,Default,Rinko,0000,0000,0000,,All right, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.81,0:15:24.73,Default,Kazuto/Asuna/Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.46,0:15:45.46,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.97,0:15:51.34,Default,Kirito,0000,0000,0000,,Outer space?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.51,0:15:56.47,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Kirito...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.35,0:15:58.27,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,look there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.06,0:16:03.06,Default,Asuna,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.73,0:16:07.86,DefaultRaised,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Star World Year 582
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.56,0:16:43.39,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,O World! Underworld where I was born\Nand which I love! Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.56,0:16:46.56,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,I have returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.94,0:16:52.53,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,I... am here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:08.75,DefaultRaised,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Integrity Pilot  Stica Schtrinen
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.09,0:17:13.13,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,Laura! Laura, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:15.09,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine, Sti.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.30,0:17:19.05,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm safe. But this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.55,0:17:19.05,DefaultRaised,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Integrity Pilot  Laurannei Arabel
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.81,0:17:21.31,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,...can't fly anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.93,0:17:23.89,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,You have no choice but to abandon ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.27,0:17:27.48,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,The thrusters on your outfit should be enough\Nto get you back to Cardina.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:28.36,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,Not happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.77,0:17:30.94,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.28,0:17:33.36,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,I can't just abandon her and flee!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.03,0:17:36.41,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,No. No, you can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:40.41,DefaultHigh,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Mythic Spacebeast  The Abyssal Horror
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.78,0:17:43.25,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's fight to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.50,0:17:46.46,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.85,0:18:10.69,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,Is that... a human?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.62,0:18:27.79,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me he's going to fight with swords?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.04,0:18:33.75,Default,Kirito,0000,0000,0000,,Release Recollection.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.82,0:18:54.11,Default,Kirito,0000,0000,0000,,Release Recollection!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.27,0:19:33.81,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,D-Did they kill it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.65,0:19:36.23,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,A monster like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.53,0:19:38.49,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, not yet!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:43.82,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,No! Don't let it get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.41,0:19:46.79,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,We have to burn all of them up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.84,0:20:00.80,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,I know this swordswoman... no, this knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.47,0:20:02.51,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.18,0:20:05.47,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,Lady... Alice?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.68,0:20:10.27,Default,Alice,0000,0000,0000,,Release Recollection.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.08,0:20:31.50,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.72,0:20:49.64,Default,Laurannei,0000,0000,0000,,Sti, I know him. I know who that person is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.97,0:20:54.19,Default,Stica,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Laura. So do I. So do I!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.92,0:22:41.54,Default,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}This is where the story ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.54,0:22:47.30,Default,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But the battle continues for Kirito,\NAsuna, Leafa, Sinon and the others,\Nas well as for Alice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.30,0:22:53.06,Default,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}They will next take up their swords\Non the final, greatest battle of all,\Nthe "Inter-Intelligence War,"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.06,0:22:58.81,Default,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}but as of this moment,\Nevery possibility is but a faint flicker,\Nwavering beyond a fluctuating light.
